<section id="judging-criteria" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="judging-criteria"><strong>Judging Criteria</strong></h2>
<ol type="1">
<li><p><strong>Creativity and Originality</strong>: How creatively has code been used to create or enhance artistic expression?</p></li>
<li><p><strong>Technical Execution</strong>: How well is the code implemented to achieve the artistic vision? Is it technically proficient and well-crafted?</p></li>
<li><p><strong>Interactivity and Engagement</strong>: Does the code-driven artwork engage the audience or user in an interactive and immersive manner?</p></li>
<li><p><strong>Innovation and Novelty</strong>: Does the use of code push the boundaries of traditional artistic mediums or introduce new ways of experiencing art?</p></li>
<li><p><strong>Aesthetics and Visual Impact</strong>: How visually appealing and impactful is the final output? Does the code contribute positively to the artistic aesthetics?</p></li>
</ol>


</section>
</section>

